Description: Concave lip and wall sherd of Attic black-glazed pottery Castulo cup; lip sharply offset on interior at lower level than inset on exterior; slightly thickened at rim; wholly glazed; inscription cut on exterior.
Bibliographic references: Gardner 1888 / Naukratis II (p. 66, no. 813, pl. XXI,)
Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 688, no. 461, pl. 22.2.20)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GA.1621)
